Package: flowEMMi
Type: Package
Title: automated model-based clustering for microbial cytometric data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Joachim Ludwig, Christian Hoener zu Siederdissen
Maintainer: Christian Hoener zu Siederdissen <choener@bioinf.uni-leipzig.de>
Description:
    flowEMMi clusters microbial cytometric data. It is designed to be time-efficient with low
    wall-clock times. In flowEMMi, we use a multivariate Gaussian mixture model, subsampling to
    speed up initial cluster determination, and perform a foreground/background separation step. The
    underlying model has been implemented in C++ and achieves running times that allow for
    near-online results.
    https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s12859-019-3152-3
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
